headline: Fastenal misses estimates amid sluggish demand for industrial safety products
summary: Shares of the Winona, Minnesota-based company fell 5.7% in premarket trading.  "Slow rate of growth was exacerbated by many of our largest customers enacting unusually sharp production cuts in the last two weeks of December during holiday-related plant shutdowns," Fastenal said.  Sales of fasteners, one of the core segments of the wholesale distributor, fell to 29.9% of the company's total sales, compared with 31.1% a year earlier.
